 During their quiz nights in May and June, The Pub managed to raised R2 100 for the Nelspruit SPCA. They also managed to collect five kilograms of food for this worthy cause. “Thanks to Ryan’s Pet Care, we managed to buy 145 kilograms of dog food with the money that was raised,” The Pub’s owner, Ettienne Coetzee, said. ALSO READ: Nelspruit SPCA still low on food He thanked everyone who participated and supported this initiative. To support the local SPCA, they can be phoned at 013-753-3582 or be visited at 6 Meidlinger Street. ALSO READ: GALLERY: Comfy laps for kittens at SPCA  